<h2>Mojito</h2>
<img src="Mojito.jpg" height=200 width=200 align= "middle">
<h3> Everyone should know how to make a Mojito. </h3>
<h2> Ingredients</h2>
<h3> Juice of one Lime </h3>
<h3> 1 tsp of granulated sugar </h3>
<h3> Small handful of mint leaves (Save one for garnishing!) </h3>
<h3> 60ml of white rum </h3>
<h3> Soda water to taste  </h3>
<h2> Instructions </h2>
<h3>Crush the lime juice, sugar and mint leaves in a small jug. You can use the end of a rolling pin or a muddler if you’re fancy. Pour this into a tall glass and add a handful of ice. </h3>

<h3>Pour over the rum, stir with a spoon and top up with soda water. Garnish with mint. </h3>
<h3> Enjoy! Try not to use a straw to save the turtles and other various marine life...</h3>
